sentences: Xhensila Myrtezaj (Albanian: [dʒɛnˈsila myɾˈtɛzaj]; born 9 April 1993), also known mononymously as Xhensila, is an Albanian singer, model and entrepreneur.
Myrtezaj was born on 9 April 1993 in Tirana, Albania, to Albanian parents, who divorced when she was a child.
Myrtezaj was born on 9 April 1993 in Tirana, Albania, to Albanian parents, who divorced when she was a child. At an early age, she attended the Jordan Misja Lyceum in Tirana.
In 2010 Myrtezaj sang A Me Do?
In 2011 she took part in Top Fest 8 with the song Engjëlli and won the Best Song Award in the Pop / R & B area.
In December 2011, Myrtezaj took part in the Albanian preliminary selection for the Eurovision Song Contest 2012, Festivali i Këngës with the song "Lulet mbledh për hënën".
In November 2016, she released "Uh Baby" with Kosovo-Albanian singer Kida.
In June 2018 she sang "Çika Çika" with Ardian Bujupi.
On 12 July 2018, she gave birth to their daughter Ajka.
